(236, 1, 'Amaryl MV 2mg Tablet', '<h2 class=\"DrugOverview__title___1OwgG\" clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" color:=\"\" rgb(33,=\"\" 33,=\"\" 33);=\"\" text-transform:=\"\" uppercase;=\"\" padding-top:=\"\" 16px;\"=\"\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px;\">INTRODUCTION</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px;\"><br></p><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 14px;=\"\" padding:=\"\" 8px=\"\" 0px=\"\" 16px;=\"\" overflow-wrap:=\"\" break-word;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Amaryl MV 2mg Tablet belongs to a category of medicines known as anti-diabetic drugs. It is a combination of two medicines used to treat type 2 diabetes mellitus in adults. It helps control blood sugar levels in people with diabetes. Keep taking this medicine, even if you feel well or your blood sugar levels are controlled. If you stop it without consulting your doctor, your blood sugar levels could rise and put you at risk of kidney damage, blindness, nerve problems and loss of limbs. Remember that it is only part of a treatment program that should also include a healthy diet, regular exercise, and weight reduction as advised by your doctor. Your lifestyle plays a big part in controlling diabetes.</div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 14px;=\"\" padding:=\"\" 8px=\"\" 0px=\"\" 16px;=\"\" overflow-wrap:=\"\" break-word;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\"><br></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 14px;=\"\" padding