(8712, 1, 'Zoryl-M4 Tablet', '<div style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: \" clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\"><div id=\"overview\"><div class=\"DrugPane__content___3-yrB\" style=\"padding: 0px 24px 24px;\"><div class=\"DrugOverview__container___CqA8x\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><h2 class=\"DrugOverview__title___1OwgG\" style=\"font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(33, 33, 33); text-transform: uppercase; padding-top: 16px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">INTRODUCTION</h2><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Zoryl-M4 Tablet&nbsp; belongs to a category of medicines known as anti-diabetic drugs. It is a combination of two medicines used to treat type 2 diabetes mellitus in adults. It helps control blood sugar levels in people with diabetes.<br></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;\">USES OF ZORYL M TABLET&nbsp;</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">In Type 2 diabetes mellitus</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Zoryl-M4 Tablet&nbsp; is a combination medicine that increases the amount of insulin your body produces (in the pancreas). The insulin then works to lower your blood glucose level.Lowering blood glucose levels is an essential part of managing diabetes. If you can control the level you will reduce the risk of getting any of the serious complications of diabetes such as kidney damage, eye damage, nerve problems, and loss of limbs.</div></div></div></div></div>', 'https://4med.in/public/assets/images/product/120321_07_20_13.jpg', '', 274.5