(8758, 1, 'Zyrop 10000 Injection', '<h2 class=\"DrugOverview__title___1OwgG\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(33, 33, 33); text-transform: uppercase; padding-top: 16px;\">INTRODUCTION</h2><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Zyrop 10000IU Injection is a medicine that helps your bone marrow to produce more red blood cells. It is used to treat a type of anemia caused by kidney disease. It is also used to treat anemia caused by cancer chemotherapy and by taking medicines to treat HIV.<br>Zyrop 10000IU Injection is given by injection either under the skin or into a vein which will be decided by your doctor. Usually, the injections are given by a nurse or doctor. The dose depends on your body weight and the cause of your anemia. Iron supplements both before and during treatment may make this treatment more effective. Zyrop 10000IU Injection needs to be stored in a fridge but used at room temperature.<br><br><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;\">USES OF ZYROP POWDER FOR INJECTION</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">In Treatment of Anemia due to chronic kidney disease</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Zyrop 10000IU Injection is a man-made protein that helps your bone marrow to produce more red blood cells. It is used to treat anemia which is caused by kidney disease in adults and children who are on dialysis. Anemia is a condition where your body does not have enough red blood cells to carry oxygen around your body. This medicine helps reduce weakness and tiredness that you may be experiencing due to anemia.&nbsp;</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">In Treatment of Anemia due to cancer chemotherapy</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Anemia is a condition where your body does not have enough red blood cells to carry oxygen around your body. Zyrop 10000IU Injection is a man-made protein that works by stimulating the bone marrow (soft tissue inside the bones) to produce more red blood cells. The natural human form of this protein may be reduced when you are having chemotherapy to treat some types of cancer. An injection of the medicine can reduce the need to have a blood transfusion.</span></div>', 'https://4med.in/public/assets/images/product/100321_10_10_33.jpg', '', 2496.30, NULL, '1 vail in packet', NULL, 1, '2021-03-10 10:33:10', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(8759, 1, 'Zyrop 2000IU Injection', '<h2 class=\"DrugOverview__title___1OwgG\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(33, 33, 33); text-transform: uppercase; padding-top: 16px;\">INTRODUCTION</h2><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Zyrop 2000IU Injection is a medicine that helps your bone marrow to produce more red blood cells. It is used to treat a type of anemia caused by kidney disease. It is also used to treat anemia caused by cancer chemotherapy and by taking medicines to treat HIV.<br>Zyrop 2000IU Injection is given by injection either under the skin or into a vein which will be decided by your doctor. Usually, the injections are given by a nurse or doctor. The dose depends on your body weight and the cause of your anemia. Iron supplements both before and during treatment may make this treatment more effective. Zyrop 2000IU Injection needs to be stored in a fridge but used at room temperature.<br><br><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;\">USES OF ZYROP POWDER FOR INJECTION</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">In Treatment of Anemia due to chronic kidney disease</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Zyrop 2000IU Injection is a man-made protein that helps your bone marrow to produce more red blood cells. It is used to treat anemia which is caused by kidney disease in adults and children who are on dialysis. Anemia is a condition where your body does not have enough red blood cells to carry oxygen around your body. This medicine helps reduce weakness and tiredness that you may be experiencing due to anemia. </span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">In Treatment of Anemia due to cancer chemotherapy</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Anemia is a condition where your body does not have enough red blood cells to carry oxygen around your body. Zyrop 2000IU Injection is a man-made protein that works by stimulating the bone marrow (soft tissue inside the bones) to produce more red blood cells. The natural human form of this protein may be reduced when you are having chemotherapy to treat some types of cancer. An injection of the medicine can reduce the need to have a blood transfusion.</span></div>', 'https://4med.in/public/assets/images/product/100321_10_42_29.jpg', '', 647.73, NULL, '2 ml in 1 vail', NULL, 1, '2021-03-10 10:29:42', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(8760, 1, 'Zyrop 4000 Injection', '<h2 class=\"DrugOverview__title___1OwgG\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 14px; color: rgb(33, 33, 33); text-transform: uppercase; padding-top: 16px;\">INTRODUCTION</h2><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Zyrop 4000 Injection is a medicine that helps your bone marrow to produce more red blood cells. It is used to treat a type of anemia caused by kidney disease. It is also used to treat anemia caused by cancer chemotherapy and by taking medicines to treat HIV.<br>Zyrop 4000 Injection is given by injection either under the skin or into a vein which will be decided by your doctor. Usually, the injections are given by a nurse or doctor. The dose depends on your body weight and the cause of your anemia. Iron supplements both before and during treatment may make this treatment more effective. Zyrop 4000 Injection needs to be stored in a fridge but used at room temperature.<br><br><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 33, 33); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase;\">USES OF ZYROP POWDER FOR INJECTION</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">In Treatment of Anemia due to chronic kidney disease</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Zyrop 4000 Injection is a man-made protein that helps your bone marrow to produce more red blood cells. It is used to treat anemia which is caused by kidney disease in adults and children who are on dialysis. Anemia is a condition where your body does not have enough red blood cells to carry oxygen around your body. This medicine helps reduce weakness and tiredness that you may be experiencing due to anemia.&nbsp;</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">In Treatment of Anemia due to cancer chemotherapy</span></div><div class=\"DrugOverview__content___22ZBX\" style=\"font-size: 14px; padding: 8px 0px 16px; overflow-wrap: break-word;\"><span clear=\"\" sans\",=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" helvetica,=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif;\"=\"\" style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102);\">Anemia is a condition where your body does not have enough red blood cells to carry oxygen around your body. Zyrop 4000 Injection is a man-made protein that works by stimulating the bone marrow (soft tissue inside the bones) to produce more red blood cells. The natural human form of this protein may be reduced when you are having chemotherapy to treat some types of cancer. An injection of the medicine can reduce the need to have a blood transfusion.</span></div>', 'https://4med.in/public/assets/images/product/100321_10_12_23.jpg', '', 1526.50, NULL, '1 vail in packet', NULL, 1, '2021-03-10 10:24:26', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
